<!-- Game Cheats Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
          		<br><u><i><font color="#FFFF00">MISC CODES:</font></i></u><br>
			&nbsp; Nereid's Labyrinth -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00">To unlock this dreaded dungeon, you must complete the game once, unlock the New Game +, and play the game. It is located on Orbus Barrier.</font>&nbsp;
			<br>&nbsp; Automatically win the sushi contest -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00">In Tinnsia, while participating in the "expensive sushi" contest with Kong the Man, play the contest through normally, eating (or not eating) any sushi you choose. -- When time runs out and BEFORE the "LOSE!" appears on the results screen, press triangle. -- The scene will return to Reid and Kong the Man in the building -- however, whether you actually won or lost the mini-game, Kong the Man will treat the results as though you won, congratulate you on a job well done, and award you the title! This glitch may be repeated as many times as the mini-game is played, although the title will only be rewarded once.</font>&nbsp;
			<br>&nbsp; Access New Game+ without playing twice -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00">To be able to access New Game+ without having to play the game twice, complete the game all the way past the six elementer pillars in Shisel's Castle. Then activate the lift. Enter the dungeon, but DO NOT go any furthur than the first screen. It should look like a purple stairway. Then, simply exit the dungeon the same way you came in and your file should be in New Game+ mode.</font>&nbsp;<br>
          		<br><u><i><font color="#FFFF00">ACTION REPLAY CODES:</font></i></u><br>
			&nbsp; Max HP Reid -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00"><br>8013FCEA 270F<br>8013FCEC 270F</font>&nbsp;
			<br>&nbsp; Max HP Farah -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00"><br>8013FDB8 270F<br>8013FDBA 270F</font>&nbsp;
			<br>&nbsp; Max HP Meredy -
                  &nbsp; <font color="#00FF00"><br>8013FF58 270F<br>8013FF5A 270F</font>&nbsp;<br>
<br>&nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
       	</td>

     </tr>
</table>

